        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 31 at 2:24PM PDT until July 31 at 3:15PM PDT by NWS Spokane WA</headline>
        <description>SVROTX

The National Weather Service in Spokane has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
West central Shoshone County in the Panhandle of Idaho...
East central Kootenai County in the Panhandle of Idaho...

* Until 315 PM PDT.

* At 224 PM PDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 9 miles northeast
of Fourth Of July Pass, or 13 miles northwest of Pinehurst, and is
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

* This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
west central Shoshone and east central Kootenai Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
